summary.narrativeincludeclinical:
22 Jun 2006 Initial report received: Legal case. Attorney reported that a Zometa patient developed osteonecrosis of the mandible or jaw bone. The attorney reported that because of the patient's multiple myeloma, the ancillary mouth and jaw infections that accompany osteonecrosis of the jaw present a particulary dangerous threat to the patient's health and well-being. The patient suffered severe pain and discomfort, difficultly in ingesting food, exposed bone in his jaw, and disfiguration as a result of the osteonecrosis.
09 Sep 2008: Follow-up information was received from an attorney in the form of medical records from the physician. The start date of Zometa was not specified. On 24 Feb 1999 the patient presented to the physician's office for evaluation of ulcers and open sores on the left lateral leg for approximately several months. He had ulcerative plaques over the left lower leg measuring 2.5 X 3.0 cm and 2.5 cm, respectively. These were thought to be secondary to trauma with slow healing due to the location as well as him being on prednisone. Treatment of trovafloxacin, topical aluminium acetate, and mupirocin was started. On 15 Jul 1999 the patient presented for evaluation of dehydration, confusion and diaphoresis. He complained of weakness and being febrile. The patient was then admitted for observation, intravenous antibiotics, and pan culture (results unspecified). On 03 Aug 1999 the patient presented six weeks after having a leg ulcer from a canine injury. The ulcer was notably infected with staphylococcus aureus and the patient was started on sulfamethoxazole and trimethoprim, topical aluminium acetate, and mupirocin. On 07 Dec 1999 the patient presented at the office for follow up and the left posterior calf was not healing for the past one to two weeks. On 11 Jan 2000 the patient presented in the office for evaluation of a cyst on the back of the leg as well as some tremulousness and arthritis. The patient's cyst was healing. On 13 Mar 2000 the patient underwent a bone marrow exam and it was found that the plasma cells increased up to 10% to 15%. On 04 Apr 2000 the patient was evaluated for a rash on the legs as well as possible skin tags and genital warts. The patient was recently diagnosed with anemia and questionable multiple myeloma. The patient had lost a lot of weight (unspecified). On 23 Jan 2001 the patient presented for evaluation, status-post multiple myeloma following a stem cell transplant. Patient was doing well on prednisone. On 13 Feb 2001 the patient was evaluated for a burning tongue. He had recently stopped prednisone (date unspecified). On examination, the patient had a slight yellowish discoloration of the tongue. On 25 Jan 2007 the patient was in a rehabilitation facility with complaint of constant pain across shoulders, neck and back. The symptoms began 7 years ago but had progressively worsened since due to rheumatoid arthritis, osteoarthritis and multiple myeloma. On an unspecified date the patient experienced atrial fibrillation, verrucous papules over genitals, fibromyalgia, hypertension, back injury, appendectomy, multiple fractures NOS, Type III Fitzpatrick's skin, total bilateral knee replacement, rheumatoid arthritis bone cancer, osteoporosis, right shoulder replacement, left hip replacement, left foot surgery; bunionectomy. The patient was on concomitant medications prednisone, digoxin, amoxicillin clavulanate, tetanus shot, methadone, buspirone, propoxyphene napsylate and acetaminophen, amitriptyline, celecoxib, clonazepam, and hydrocodone and acetaminophen. No further information was provided.
Follow-up information received on 08 Dec 2008 from the patient's attorney, inclusive of medical records: On 07 Jun 2000 the patient initiated Aredia IV monthly for ongoing steroid-induced osteoporosis (dosing unknown). The patient was now taking three regimens for osteoporosis including Miacalcin nasal spray, Actonel and monthly Aredia. In 1999 the patient developed cellulitis and shingles. In 2000 the patient developed hypogonadism, weight loss of 45 pounds over eight months, steroid abuse and bone pain. The bone pain was treated with Methadone. On an unspecified date, the patient developed steroid induced osteoporosis, rib and vertebral fractures, depression and degenerative disc disease. No further information was provided.
Follow-up information received on 08 May 2009 from the patient's attorney, inclusive of medical records. Medical history updated with multiple myeloma; May 2000 and stem cell transplant, arthritis, psoriasis, depression, chronic pain syndrome, multiple compression fractures, obstructive sleep disorder, paroxymal atrial fibrillation, kidney stones, GERD, hypogonadism, elevated liver enzymes, pneumonia, appendectomy, tonsillectomy, prednisone dependant, chronic periodontitis, root canal therapy, osteopenia previous use of chemotherapy. Records dated 21 Dec 2004 noted the patient experienced chest pain. Records dated 02 Mar 2006 noted a small sequestrum was removed. Records dated 24 Mar 2006 noted the patient was diagnosed with osteonecrosis of the mandible. Records dated 03 Oct 2006 noted the patient experienced some heart trouble. Records dated 24 Jan 2007 noted the patient's filling fell out of tooth. Records dated 11 Apr 2007 noted the patient experienced gum recession around #31 area. Records dated 19 Apr 2007 noted the patient experienced lip lesion.
Follow up received on 23 Apr 2010 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Records dated 17 Apr 2007 noted the patient had cataract in both eyes and experienced blurred vision. He underwent cataract surgery in the right eye on 07 Jul 2007 and in the left eye on 07 Jun 2007. Records dated 02 Jul 2007 noted the patient experienced blurred vision post op cataract surgery (left eye). Records dated 14 Aug 2007 noted the patient experienced blurriness in the peripheral vision for several weeks and felt dizzy. He also used Visine for dry eyes.
Follow-up report received on 09 Jun 2010 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Past medical history included hyperlipidemia, embolus, deviated septum surgery, eczema, bilateral hand surgery, cervical spine fusion, inguinal hernia replacement, umbilical hernia repair, peripheral neuropathy, steroid induced myopathy, inflammatory polyarthritis, right ankle fusion, ADHD, testosterone deficiency, thoracic vertebroplastsy, and family history of diabetes mellitus. Concomitant medications updated. Records dated 09 Mar 2004 reported basal cell carcinoma. The patient had a reverse right total arthoplasty on 20 Dec 2004 due to failed right total shoulder arthroplasty and a catheter was inserted through the right jugular vein. Records dated 20 Dec 2004 reported decreased calcium, decreased albumin, chronic left hand edema, microscopic hematuria, and azotemia. Records dated 14 May 2004 reported status post open reduction internal fixation of right proximal radius fracture. Records dated 11 Jun 2004 reported warts. The patient had been diagnosed with constipation and neuropathic pain involving the left hand as sequelae of herpes virus infection on an unspecified date. Relevant lab data included a CPK of 264 and 254 (range: 0-170) on 21 Dec 2004. Treatment medications included Demerol, morphine sulfate, bacitracin, Solu-cortef, Ancef, Dilaudid, Procrit, acyclovir, clonidine, and Arava. No further information was provided.
Follow-up report received from the consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records/ laboratory records on 09 Jul 2010. Records dated on 08 Dec 2005 reported medical history of kyphosis and condylomata. The patient had left knee wound. Records dated on 10 Dec 2005 updated concomitant drug information.
Follow up received on 29 Jun 2010 from the consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: Psychiatric assessment dated 27 Apr 2006 indicated major depressive disorder (recurrent episode, severe and without psychosis) and generalized anxiety disorder; Ambien and Cymbalta were prescribed. Concomitant medications were updated.
Follow-up records received from the consumer's attorney on 16 Jul 2010 inclusive of medical records: Records dated 01 Dec 2004 noted that the consumer's depression was under reasonably control but that he still had attentional difficulties. Records dated 13 Dec 2004 noted that the consumer felt more depressed. On an unspecified date, the consumer fell and "his arm was in a sling." Records dated 17 Feb 2006 noted that the consumer's jaw bone was open and would not adequately heal. Records dated 26 Oct 2006 noted that the consumer had hand surgery (not specified). Records dated 29 Mar 2007 noted that the consumer was agitated. Records dated 06 Jun 2007 noted that the consumer had extreme anger but not depression. Records dated 12 Nov 2007 noted that the consumer had developed a "fistula" between his bladder and bowel. He fell while outside and fractured ribs. Records dated 30 Jan 2008 noted that the consumer was pale and had lost weight.
Follow-up report received form the consumer's attorney on 22 Sep 2010 inclusive of dental records: Records dated 30 Jun 2005 noted that the consumer had teeth #31 and #10 evaluated. It was unclear if the consumer had an active lesion or an apical scar.
Follow up received on 11 Nov 2010 from the consumers attorney inclusive of medical records: Medical records dated 04 Jun 2001, C7-T1 had cervical radicular pain syndrome. On 05 Dec 2005, patient underwent bone graft in the left knee donor site and developed AHCPR stage 111 left foot medial and lateral ulcerations secondary to post operative skin flap and had hyperbaric treatment. Medical records also reported that the patient broke leg, arm, nose, throat and both hands. The consumer's medical records also inclusive of updates of concomitant medications.
Follow-up received on 30 Nov 2010 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Records dated 20 Oct 1997 stated that the patient had cervical spondylosis, disc protrusion at C4-5. Records dated 30 May 2000 stated that the patient had hemangioma, spinal stenosis. Records dated 31 May 2000 stated that the patient had marrow edema in proximal ulna. Records dated 04 Nov 2000 stated that the patient had hypokalemia. Records dated 31 Oct 2000 stated that the patient had dilated left ventricle.
Follow up report received on 18 May 2011 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. The patient's medical history and procedures were updated. The patient's concomitant medications of metoprolol, Coumadin (warfarin sodium), amiodarone, Diflucan (fluconazole), Flomax (tamsulosin hydrochloride) and lidocaine were also updated. Records dated on 07 Mar 2008 stated that the patient had bacterial sepsis (anaerobic septicemia), diarrhea, mild disseminated intravascular coagulation, recurrent atelectasis in both lung bases, bilateral small pleural effusions, hepatic cysts, dysphagia, cardiac arrhythmia, decreased cardiac output, oral thrush, acute renal failure and urinary tract infection. Records dated on 12 Mar 2008 stated patient had thrombocytopenia and records dated on 14 Mar 2008 stated patient had coronary artery disease and benign prostatic hypertrophy. Records dated on 20 Mar 2008 stated that the patient had esophageal dismobility/stricture and severe malnutrition. Records dated on 29 Mar 2008 stated that the patient had abdominal pain and small bowel obstruction. The outcome of the events were not reported.
Follow up report received on 14 Jul 2011 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Records dated 18 Jun 1999 noted puffy, swollen and painful gums. Upper right mid to back teeth were sensitive. Sensodyne was given. The outcome of the events was not reported.
Follow up information received from a consumer's attorney on 29 Jul 2011 inclusive of medical records. Records dated Sep 2005 stated the patient had abscessed tooth. The outcome for the event was not reported.
Follow-up received on 05 Apr 2012 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. The dose and frequency of Aredia and Zometa was updated. The patient received Zometa for osteoporosis. The record dated 04 Nov 2002 noted lymphedema in patient. The record dated 07 Nov 2002 stated that the patient had gait disorder. Records dated 18 Dec 2002 stated that the patient experienced chest congestion, cough and shortness of breath and received treatment with Levaquin. The record further stated that the patient had migraine. The record dated 25 Mar 2003 stated that the patient suffered decreased hearing from the left ear. Records dated 13 Jun 2003 stated that the patient had penile wart which was removed by shave biopsy on 13 Jun 2003. The record dated 12 Jan 2004 noted bacterial conjunctivitis in patient. The outcome of the events was not reported.
Follow-up report received from the consumer’s attorney on 20 Nov 2012 inclusive of medical records. Record dated 01 Nov 2006 noted that the patient complaint of cirrhosis liver. Record dated 27 Feb 2007 noted that the patient had mild splenomegaly. Record dated 30 Aug 2007 revealed that the patient suffered from myelopathy. Record dated 18 Oct 2007 noted that the patient had rectorrhagia. Record dated 06 Nov 2007 stated that the patient diagnosed with dermatoheliosis and psoriasiform dermatitis. Record dated 06 Dec 2007 noted that the patient suffered from pathological rib fracture and colovesical fistula. Record dated 27 Dec 2007 noted that the patient complaint of bleeding from eye. Outcome of the events was not reported.
Follow-up received on 28 Nov 2012 from consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Record dated 24 Oct 2001 stated that the patient had central canal stenosis at the L3, facet joint hypertrophy and mild hallux valgus. Record dated 29 Jan 2002 stated that the patient had diverticulosis and tiny nodule in the left lung base. Record dated 27 Mar 2002 stated that the patient developed sclerosis involving the acetabulum. Record dated 07 Oct 2002 stated that the patient developed generalized tenosynovitis left wrist. Record dated 25 Mar 2003 stated that the patient had coronary artery calcification. Record dated 23 Jun 2004 stated that the patient had bilateral varicoceles and left epididymal cyst. The outcome of the events was not reported.
Follow up received on 29 Nov 2012 via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Patient had received Aredia (disodium pamidronate) for the treatment osteoporosis in 2000 at a dose of 90 mg IV, QMO. Record dated 19 Dec 2002 noted that patient had received Zometa for the treatment of multiple myeloma in Aug 2002. Record dated 23 Jan 2003 noted that patient was suffering from tracheal bronchitis. Record dated 26 Mar 2003 noted that patient underwent cerumen removal from ear canals (date not specified). Record dated 28 Mar 2003 noted that patient was suffering from cerumen impaction both ears. Record dated 08 May 2003 noted that patient suffered from rotator cuff tear. Record dated 15 May 2003 noted that patient suffered from poikiloderma of civatte. Record dated 17 Nov 2003 noted that patient was suffering from calluses right foot. Treatment with Zometa was discontinued on 04 Feb 2004. The outcome of the events was not reported.
Please refer split case id PHEH2012US023973 created for Aredia
